<section id="deploy">
  <div class="sh"><div class="sh-n">06</div><div class="sh-t">Deploy in 10 minutes</div></div>
  <div class="deploy-wrap">
    <div class="deploy-grid">
      <div class="deploy-l">
        <h2 class="deploy-h">One command.<br />Your infrastructure.<br /><em>Running today.</em></h2>
        <p class="deploy-p">The deployment tooling generates your Cloudflare Worker, KV namespaces, R2 buckets, and D1 database and walks you through the DNS setup. No Cloudflare expertise required. The only prerequisite is a Cloudflare account — which you probably already have.</p>
        <p class="deploy-p">Every ad network strategy is independently configurable. Add Meta CAPI today and Google Measurement Protocol next week. Remove TikTok if you stop running TikTok ads. Each strategy reads its credentials from its own environment variables — none of them interact.</p>
        <p class="deploy-p"><strong>No redeployment for strategy updates.</strong> The Worker core is stable — strategy bundle updates arrive via CDN. Deploy once, get current strategy behavior forever.</p>
        <ul class="deploy-steps">
          <li class="deploy-step"><div class="ds-n">01</div><div class="ds-body"><strong>Clone and install.</strong> <code>git clone github.com/attestrue/attestrue</code> then <code>pnpm install</code>. TypeScript, Turborepo, standard toolchain.</div></li>
          <li class="deploy-step"><div class="ds-n">02</div><div class="ds-body"><strong>Configure your strategies.</strong> Copy <code>wrangler.toml.example</code> to <code>wrangler.toml</code>. Add the environment variables for the ad networks you use. Skip the ones you don't.</div></li>
          <li class="deploy-step"><div class="ds-n">03</div><div class="ds-body"><strong>Deploy to your CF account.</strong> <code>npx wrangler deploy</code>. Takes 30 seconds. The Worker is now running at your Cloudflare account subdomain.</div></li>
          <li class="deploy-step"><div class="ds-n">04</div><div class="ds-body"><strong>Add the DNS CNAME.</strong> Point a subdomain (<code>t.yourdomain.com</code>) to your Worker. Now it's first-party — your domain, not Cloudflare's. Not blocked by ad blockers.</div></li>
          <li class="deploy-step"><div class="ds-n">05</div><div class="ds-body"><strong>Add the browser tag.</strong> Drop the consent.js script tag in your <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>. That's it. Events start flowing.</div></li>
          <li class="deploy-step"><div class="ds-n">06</div><div class="ds-body"><strong>Optional: add ClickHouse.</strong> Spin up a ClickHouse instance (clickhouse.com free tier or self-hosted). Run the schema DDL. Add your ClickHouse URL to your Worker env. Every event now goes to your own database.</div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="deploy-r">
        <div class="code">
          <div class="code-label">Full setup — terminal</div>
          <pre set:html={`<span class="cd"># Clone the repo</span>
<span class="cg">git clone</span> github.com/attestrue/attestrue
<span class="cg">cd</span> attestrue
<span class="cg">pnpm install</span>

<span class="cd"># Copy config, add your credentials</span>
<span class="cg">cp</span> wrangler.toml.example wrangler.toml
<span class="cd"># Edit wrangler.toml with your pixel IDs</span>
<span class="cd"># and ClickHouse URL</span>

<span class="cd"># Deploy</span>
<span class="cg">npx wrangler deploy</span>
<span class="cd">✓ Deployed to: my-tracker.workers.dev</span>

<span class="cd"># Add DNS CNAME in Cloudflare dashboard:
# t.yourdomain.com → my-tracker.workers.dev
# Proxied: yes (orange cloud)
# Now first-party — not blocked</span>

<span class="cd"># Add the script tag</span>
<span class="cp">&lt;script</span> <span class="cb">src</span>=<span class="cg">"https://t.yourdomain.com/consent.js"</span><span class="cp">&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</span>

<span class="cd"># That's it. Events are flowing.
# Check your ClickHouse:
</span><span class="cg">SELECT</span> count(*), consent_state
<span class="cg">FROM</span> tracking_events
<span class="cg">WHERE</span> date = today()
<span class="cg">GROUP BY</span> consent_state;`} />
        </div>
        <div class="migration-box">
          <div class="migration-label">Migrating from Stape / Elevar / Addingwell?</div>
          <div class="migration-body">The strategies map 1:1 to what those platforms do. The difference: your credentials don't leave your account, there's no monthly fee, and you get the ClickHouse pipeline for free. Migration guide in the docs.</div>
          <a href="#" class="migration-link">Migration guide &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

